definition.value: Catalysis of the reaction -  alpha-D-mannose 1-phosphate + GTP -eq- diphosphate + GDP-alpha-D-mannose.

Catalysis of the reaction -  S-adenosyl-L-methionine + G(5')pppR-RNA -eq- S-adenosyl-L-homocysteine + m7G(5')pppR-RNA. m7G(5')pppR-RNA is mRNA containing an N7-methylguanine cap -  R may be guanosine or adenosine.
Catalysis of the reaction -  S-adenosyl-L-methionine + m7G(5')pppR-RNA -eq- S-adenosyl-L-homocysteine + m7G(5')pppRm-RNA. R may be guanosine or adenosine.

Catalysis of the reaction -  GTP + (5')pp-Pur-mRNA -eq- diphosphate + G(5')ppp-Pur-mRNA -  G(5')ppp-Pur-mRNA is mRNA containing a guanosine residue linked 5' through three phosphates to the 5' position of the terminal residue.

Catalysis of the reaction -  D-glucose 6-phosphate -eq- 1D-myo-inositol 3-phosphate. This reaction requires NAD, which dehydrogenates the CHOH group to CO at C-5 of the glucose 6-phosphate, making C-6 into an active methylene, able to condense with the aldehyde at C-1. Finally, the enzyme-bound NADH reconverts C-5 into the CHOH form.

Catalysis of the reaction -  CMP-N-acetylneuraminate + beta-D-galactosyl-1,4-N-acetyl-beta-D-glucosaminyl-1,3-beta-D-galactosyl-1,4-beta-D-glucosylceramide -eq- CMP + alpha-N-acetylneuraminyl-2,3-beta-D-galactosyl-1,4-N-acetyl-beta-D-glucosaminyl-1,3-beta-D-galactosyl-1,4-D-glucosylceramide.

Catalysis of the reaction -  diphosphate + nicotinate D-ribonucleotide -eq- 5-phospho-alpha-D-ribose 1-diphosphate + H(+) + nicotinate.
Catalysis of the reaction -  L-arginine + n NADPH + n H+ + m O2 -eq- citrulline + nitric oxide + n NADP+.
